            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Actually don't see a bug. Does the log have a warning in it? \n\n`stdpaths_user_state_subpath(\"nvim.log\", 0, true)` correctly produces `~/.local/state/nvim/nvim.log`. And this is covered by tests...\n\nIf you are seeing `nvim.log` in CWD, that implies that previously `.nvimlog` was also in CWD, maybe you didn't notice it because it is dot-prefixed?\n\nDoes nvim have write permissions to `stdpath('log')` ? \n\n    :echo getfperm(stdpath('log'))\n",
