        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "That's odd, I checked and verified that `.nvimlog` didn't exist after reading through the git diff of the commit. It would have shown up in git status previously, so I'm pretty sure that that has never happened before.\n\n`:echo getfperm(stdpath('log'))` outputs `rwx------`, and commits before the mentioned commit also write to the old `~/.local/state/nvim/log` file, I checked and opening a new clean instance with `nvim --clean` appends the same\n\n```\nWRN 2026-02-24T10:17:35.750 ui.24489   tui_handle_term_mode:239: TUI: terminal mode 2048 detected, state 2\n```\n\nwhich appears in the `nvim.log` file in the current working directory after the commit.",
